<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Often found boring in oysters. Type locality: Mediterranean (Gulf of Naples). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Sato-Okoshi et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, in agreement with the taxonomic observations of 
<bibRefCitation author="Radashevsky, Vasily I." journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="859 - 868" title="First report of the polychaete Polydorahoplura (Annelida: Spionidae) from North and South America and Asian Pacific" volume="47" year="2016">Radashevsky and Migotto (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, provided molecular evidence that 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora uncinata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="uncinata">Polydora uncinata</taxonomicName>
Sato-Okoshi, 1998 is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora hoplura" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hoplura">Polydora hoplura</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
